{{Infobox Diplomatic Mission |name = Delegation of the European Union to Canada |image = |caption = |address = 150 [[Metcalfe Street (Ottawa)|Metcalfe Street]], Suite 1900 |location = [[Ottawa|Ottawa, Ontario]] |coordinates = {{coord|45.4214|N|75.6983|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |ambassador = }}
The '''Delegation of the European Union to Canada''' is located in [[Ottawa|Ottawa, Ontario]], Canada. It was established to facilitate relations between the [[European Union]] and [[Canada]]. It opened in 1976 and was originally located at 45 [[O'Connor Street]] before moving to a new location at 150 Metcalfe Street.
Though not officially an embassy, the head of the mission is given rank and courtesy title of [[ambassador]] within Canadian law. The Delegation has three sections: Economic and Trade; Political and Public Affairs; and Administration.
