The '''Independence Party of America''' '''(IPA)''' was a [[political party]] in the [[United States]], founded on September 23, 2007 as a coalition of existing state parties bearing the Independence Party name.  Its National Chairman was Frank MacKay, chairman of the [[Independence Party of New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.midhudsonnews.com/News/IndParAm-24Sep07.html |date= September 24, 2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071219035016/http://www.midhudsonnews.com/News/IndParAm-24Sep07.html |archivedate=December 19, 2007 |title= Independence Party of America formed |work= Mid-Hudson News |publisher= Mid-Hudson News Network }}</ref> [[Dean Barkley]], a former [[United States Senator]] and [[Independence Party of Minnesota]] activist, agreed to play an advisory role with the new party.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://weblogs.newsday.com/news/local/longisland/politics/blog/independence_party/ |title= Indie strategists are coming from LI local, trying US global |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071231185036/http://weblogs.newsday.com/news/local/longisland/politics/blog/independence_party/ |date= October 16, 2007 |work= Newsday |archivedate= December 31, 2007 }}</ref>

The Independence Party of Minnesota voted to affiliate with the new national party at its state convention on January 26, 2008, though it later disafilliated.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ballot-access.org/2008/01/13/virginia-independent-green-party-affiliates-with-independence-party/ |title= Virginia Independent Green Party Affiliates with Independence Party |date= January 13, 2008 |work= Ballot Access News }}</ref> The Reform Party of Pennsylvania affiliated on October 22, 2007<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ballot-access.org/2007/10/23/pennsylvania-reform-party-affiliates-with-new-national-independence-party/ |work= Ballot Access News |title= Pennsylvania Reform Party Affiliates with new national Independence Party |date= October 23, 2007 }}</ref> and the [[Independent Green Party of Virginia]] affiliated on January 10, 2008.<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090123232409/http://independencepartyofamerica.com/freedom/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=96&Itemid=2 |url= http://independencepartyofamerica.com/freedom/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=96&Itemid=2 |title= Independence Party of America, Bloomberg for President |work= Independence Party of America |archivedate= January 23, 2009 |date= }}</ref>

The party's website was defunct in April 2013. The various state parties each went their separate ways; for example, in the [[United States presidential election, 2016|2016 presidential election]], the Minnesota party endorsed [[Evan McMullin]] and the New York party cross-endorsed [[Libertarian Party (United States)|Libertarian]] nominee [[Gary Johnson]].

