The '''National Front for the Family''' ({{lang-es|Frente Nacional por la Familia}}) is a Mexican coalition of over 1000 organizations. Their marches have been supported by [[Pope Francis]]<ref name="lifesitenews">{{cite web|url=https://www.lifesitenews.com/news/massive-mexico-city-march-defends-the-family-against-gay-marriage-and-gende|title=Massive Mexico City pro-family march protests gay &#8216;marriage,&#8217; gender ideology &#124; News|website=LifeSite|accessdate=2018-05-22}}</ref><ref name="christianpost">{{cite web|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/pope-francis-backs-215000-catholics-protesting-mexicos-push-legalize-gay-marriage-170072/|website=christianpost.com|title=Pope Francis Backs 215,000 Catholics Protesting Mexico's Push to Legalize Gay Marriage|accessdate=2018-05-22}}</ref>
==History== The National Front for the Family formed in 2016 after Peña Nieto pushed an initiative that would've legalized same-sex marriage.<ref name="actuall">{{cite web|url=https://www.actuall.com/criterio/familia/el-frente-nacional-por-la-familia-ante-el-reto-de-mexico-2018/|author=Rodrigo Iván Cortés|website=actuall.com|title=El Frente Nacional por la Familia ante el reto de México 2018|accessdate=2018-05-22}}</ref> The initiative would've also allowed homosexuals to adopt children and established [[no-fault divorce]].<ref>{{cite web|title=¿Qué dice el Frente Nacional por la Familia? &#124; Excélsior|url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/2016/09/12/1116421|website=Excélsior|accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref> Peña Nieto's initiative was rejected by congress and his party lost 7 of 12 governorships later the same year.<ref>{{cite news|title=¿Quién es quién en la elección y la agenda de la familia? &#124; NTR Guadalajara|url=http://www.ntrguadalajara.com/post.php?id_nota=99256|accessdate=24 May 2018|date=21 May 2018}}</ref>
==Support== [[Pope Francis]] has said, "I join willingly the bishops of Mexico in supporting the efforts of the Church and civil society in favor of the family and of life, which at this time require special pastoral and cultural attention worldwide."<ref name="christianpost" />
[[Brian S. Brown]] has said, "The National March for the Family has the potential of being the largest single demonstration of support for marriage, children and parental rights in history."<ref name="nomblog">{{cite web|title=Please Sign Our Petition To Stand With Mexico To Support Marriage, Children and Parental Rights &#124; NOM Blog |url=https://www.nomblog.com/41147/|website="NOM Blog"|accessdate=22 May 2018}}</ref>
