{{Infobox video game |title = Supreme Ruler |image = Supreme Ruler TRS.jpg |developer = [[JMG Software International]] |publisher = [[JMG Software International]] |designer = George Geczy |released = October 1982 |genre = [[Strategy game|Strategy]] |modes = [[Single player]], [[multiplayer]] |platforms = [[TRS-80]] }} [[File:TRS-80-SR.jpg|thumb|Supreme Ruler running on a TRS-80 Model 4P microcomputer]] '''''Supreme Ruler''''' is a [[Computer game|computer]] [[Strategy video game|strategy game]] in which a player controls a region's [[government]] and attempts to conquer a fictional world of fragmented [[Nation state|states]]. The game simulates raising funds through taxes and spending on agriculture, government services, and the military. Up to 9 regions play at once, either human [[Hotseat (multiplayer mode)|hotseat]] or AI controlled, and all actions are resolved simultaneously at the end of each turn. The design of Supreme Ruler was influenced by earlier nation-state simulations such as [[Hamurabi|Sumer]], though the concept is taken further with the addition of multiplayer, military battles, and a more sophisticated design.
The game was created by George Geczy and produced and published by [[JMG Software International]], released for the [[TRS-80]] microcomputer system in October 1982. An updated and expanded version, '''''Supreme Ruler Plus''''', was released in May 1983.<ref>{{cite web|title=Moby Games|url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/trs-80/supreme-ruler-plus|accessdate=29 December 2011}}</ref>
==Supreme Ruler Series==
The original '''''Supreme Ruler''''' games were the inspiration for George Geczy and David Thompson to create a new, modern version of the game, for the Windows PC platform. This project began in January 2000 with the formation of [[BattleGoat Studios]] and culminated with the release of [[Supreme Ruler 2010]] in May 2005, followed by sequels [[Supreme Ruler 2020]] in June 2008, [[Supreme Ruler Cold War]] in July 2011, [[Supreme Ruler 1936]] in May 2014, [[Supreme Ruler Ultimate]] in October 2014, and [[Supreme Ruler The Great War]] in August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Supreme Ruler Ultimate on Steam|url=http://store.steampowered.com/app/314980/|website=Steam|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Developer Diary on Gamespy|url=http://www.gamespy.com/devdiary/september01/sr20101/index.shtm|accessdate=16 June 2017|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040315152533/http://www.gamespy.com/devdiary/september01/sr20101/index.shtm|archivedate=15 March 2004|df=}}</ref>
